# Tailwind CSS Styling Guidelines

## Core Principles
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Utility-first approach with component extraction when needed
- Consistent spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64px)
- Design system approach with custom CSS properties for brand colors

## Class Organization Order
1. Layout (flex, grid, block, etc.)
2. Positioning (relative, absolute, etc.)
3. Size (w-, h-, max-w-, etc.)
4. Spacing (m-, p-, gap-, etc.)
5. Typography (text-, font-, leading-, etc.)
6. Colors (bg-, text-, border-, etc.)
7. Effects (shadow-, opacity-, etc.)
8. Responsive prefixes last

## Component Structure
- Extract repeated patterns into components
- Use @apply for complex utility combinations
- Prefer semantic class names for complex components
- Keep utility classes for one-off styling

## Responsive Strategy
- Default mobile styles first
- Use sm:, md:, lg:, xl: progressively
- Test at 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px breakpoints